# Scandicommerce Project Rules

## Project
This is a Next.js + Sanity CMS v3 website for scandicommerce.no, a Shopify Plus partner agency in Norway.
The site has landing pages in 5 languages: Norwegian (no), English (en), German (de), Danish (da), Swedish (sv).

## Architecture
- Sanity schemas: `sanity/schemas/`
- Section component schemas: `sanity/schemas/components/`
- Landing page schema: `sanity/schemas/documents/landingPage.ts`
- Frontend components: check `components/` or `app/` directory
- GROQ queries: check for `.groq` files or inline queries in page components

## Coding Standards
- TypeScript strict mode
- Use `defineType`, `defineField` from `sanity` for all schema definitions
- Follow existing naming conventions (camelCase for schema names)
- Use existing CSS/styling approach — do not introduce new styling libraries
- Preserve existing component interfaces when refactoring

## Important Context
- The site is in production with real client data
- All 5 language versions share the same schema but can have different content
- Section components already exist and work — we are changing how they connect to pages, not rebuilding them
- The teal (#00d4aa) and dark (#0d1117) color scheme is the brand identity — do not change it

## When Making Changes
- Always work on a feature branch
- Explain what you are about to change before doing it
- After schema changes, verify Sanity Studio still loads
- After frontend changes, verify the dev server still renders
- If a section component expects data in a specific format, preserve that format in the SectionRenderer
